Episodes.Title: The Beginning
Episodes.Plot: Mulder is less than thrilled when an Office of Professional Conduct board refuses to reassign him and Scully to The X-Files and even more so when he learns that Agent Spender and Agent Fowley have become their successors. When Gibson Praise reappears and comes to them for help, Mulder and Scully attempt to continue their quest undercover despite having fewer friends and less access and protection than ever before.
Episodes.GuestStars: Scott Eberlein, Rick Millikan, Wayne Thomas Yorke, Wayne Alexander, Ralph Meyering Jr., Benito Martinez, Kim Robillard, Arthur Taxier, Wendie Malick

Episodes.Title: Drive
Episodes.Plot: Mulder is trapped in a car with a man who has developed a serious ear condition which can only be suppressed by driving west at high speeds. As Scully tries to find the cause and a cure for the problem, Mulder and the man get closer and closer to the ocean.
Episodes.GuestStars: Bryan Cranston, Michael O'Neill, Harry Danner, Linda Porter, Mindy Seeger, Scott A. Smith, Tim Agee, Mark Craig, Wiley Pickett, Ken Collins, Tegan West, Tom Hale, Frank Buckley, Bob Peters, Janine Venable, Art Picke

Episodes.Title: Triangle
Episodes.Plot:
Mulder goes to the Bermuda Triangle when he learns that the Queen Anne, a British luxury liner which disappeared during WWII, has reappeared in the middle of the Sargasso Sea. Mulder's boat is wrecked and after floating in the water, he is hauled aboard the ship which has just been hijacked by the Nazis searching for the man who will build the atom bomb.
Mulder tries to convince the crew that they have traveled into the future, but evidence further suggests that it is he who is back in the past.
Episodes.GuestStars: Wolfgang Gerhard, Guido Föhrweißer, Issac C. Singleton Jr., Laura Leigh Hughes, Robert Thomas Beck, Robert Arce, Madison Mason, Trevor Goddard, G.W. Stevens, Greg Ellis, Nick Meaney, Kai Wulff, Issac Charles Sing

Episodes.Title: Dreamland (1)
Episodes.Plot: While being detained near the famed "Dreamland" Area 51, a strange craft flies overhead and Mulder swaps bodies with an Area 51 "Man-in-Black". While the other agent has fun in Mulder's body, Mulder himself finds it difficult to fit into someone else's life, especially a shadowy one. Mulder contacts Scully about the body swap and tries to get her the flight data recorder from the UFO test flight, but his alter ego uses Mulder's FBI persona to have him arrested.
Episodes.Writer: Vince Gilligan, John Shiban, Frank Spotnitz
Episodes.GuestStars: Michael McKean, John Mahon, Tyler Binkley, Dara Hollingsworth, Ted White, Laura Leigh Hughes, Eddie Jackson, Christopher J. Stapleton, James Yaker, Freeman Michaels, Greg Smith, Michael B. Silver, Scott Allan Cam

Episodes.Title: Dreamland II (2)
Episodes.Plot: Mulder is thrown in jail at the Area 51 compound but is released when it is discovered that the flight data recorder he stole was a fake. Scully comes to her senses and realizes that the Mulder she sees isn't who he really is and heads back to Nevada to help the real Mulder. Meanwhile, the mechanism that caused the body swap is rapidly snapping back, undoing everything in its wake, and Mulder and his alter ego must race to put themselves back where they belong.
Episodes.Writer: Vince Gilligan, John Shiban, Frank Spotnitz
Episodes.GuestStars: Michael McKean, John Mahon, Dara Hollingsworth, Tyler Binkley, Mike Rad, Lisa Joann Thompson, Christopher J. Stapleton, Jeffrey T. Unterkofler, James Yaker, Nick Lashaway, Ashlynn Rose, Bonnie McNeil, Michael B.

Episodes.Title: How The Ghosts Stole Christmas
Episodes.Plot: Mulder talks Scully into investigating a haunted house on Christmas Eve where several couples have met their fate on that very night. While there, they encounter endless tricks and traps set by a ghostly couple who originally made a lovers suicide pact in the house. The ghosts try to convince Mulder and Scully to kill each other.
Episodes.GuestStars: Lily Tomlin, Edward Asner

Episodes.Title: Terms of Endearment
Episodes.Plot: After a scan of a couple's unborn child is found to have strange growths protruding from the head and back, the fetus is taken from inside the mother by a demon creature while she is asleep. Mulder heads to investigate after Agent Spender dismisses the claims, and discovers that the father is actually a demon who wants to have a normal child.
Episodes.GuestStars: Michael Rothhaar, Matthew Butcher, Lenora May, Jimmy Staszkiel, Karen Stone, Bruce Campbell, Lisa Jane Persky, Michael Milhoan, Grace Phillips, Jimmy Staszkiel

Episodes.Title: The Rain King
Episodes.Plot: Strange weather phenomena in a small town leads Mulder to believe that a weatherman's deep emotions and unspoken love toward his workmate are becoming real in the form of snow and tornadoes.
Episodes.GuestStars: Victoria Jackson, Clayton Rohner, David Manis, Dirk Blocker, Francesca Ingrassia, Tom McFadden, Dan Gifford, Sharon Madden, Brian D. Johnson, Sally Stevens, Geoffrey Gould

Episodes.Title: S.R. 819
Episodes.Plot: Mulder and Scully have 24 hours to save A.D. Skinner from being killed by a biologically engineered disease. The disease appears to be created by a shadowy government organization, but in order to save Skinner's life they must determine who wants him dead and why. With Skinner's condition worsening, Mulder seeks assistance from Senator Matheson, who he hopes can provide some answers and help him to find a cure.
Episodes.GuestStars: Donna Marie Moore, Greta Fadness, Dan Klass, Susana Mercedes, Tim Van Pelt, Keith Coulouris, Al Faris, Jonathan Fraser, Julie Hubert, Mickey Knox, Raymond J. Barry, John Towey, Kenneth Tigar, Jenny Gago

Episodes.Title: Tithonus
Episodes.Plot:
Assistant Director Kersh tries to tear Scully and Mulder apart when he partners Scully with a New York agent investigating Alfred Fellig, a freelance police photographer who conveniently shows up to document the scene of a death as soon as it happens.
While the young hotshot agent is convinced that Fellig is murdering the people, Scully has other (paranormal) theories.
Episodes.GuestStars: Geoffrey Lewis, Richard Ruccolo, Ange Billman, Nicky Fane, Naomi Matsuda, Matt Gallini, Coby Ryan McLaughlin, Jolyon Reese, Javier Grajeda, Barry Wiggins, Don Fehmel, Dell Yount

Episodes.Title: Two Fathers (1)
Episodes.Plot: While the Cigarette-Smoking Man recites to an unseen listener everything about the work of the Syndicate involving a global conspiracy in cooperation with an alien species, Cassandra Spender reappears and is pursued by the scientists who would rather kill her than keep her alive. Cassandra runs to Mulder's apartment and demands that he shoot her because she is the culmination of 50 years work - a living alien/human hybrid - and colonization will begin if the aliens find out about her.
Episodes.GuestStars: Damon P. Saleem, Valarie Pettiford, Veronica Cartwright, Nick Tate, Al Ruscio, Frank Ertl

Episodes.Title: One Son (2)
Episodes.Plot: The Cigarette-Smoking Man reveals all the government secrets from the past 50 years in order for his son, Jeffery Spender, to join him in his work. Mulder learns that the final stage of the conspiracy will soon begin with the hybridization of the Syndicate members, and he must stop it from happening. Agent Spender deceives his father and arranges for Mulder and Scully to be reassigned to the X-Files, which doesn't sit too well with the Cigarette-Smoking Man.
Episodes.GuestStars: Robert Lipton, Scott Williamson, Jo Black-Jacob, Mark Bramhall, Veronica Cartwright, Al Ruscio, Frank Ertl

Episodes.Title: Agua Mala
Episodes.Plot: Arthur Dales summons Mulder and Scully to his holiday home in Florida where he is concerned over the disappearance of his neighbors. Despite the raging hurricane, Mulder and Scully head out to investigate and discover several strange deaths caused by an octopus-like sea creature that swam in through the overflowing sewer system.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jeremy Roberts, Joel McKinnon Miller, Diana-Maria Riva, Valente Rodriguez, Silas Weir Mitchell, Nichole Pelerine, Max Kasch, Darren McGavin, Allen Cutler

Episodes.Title: Monday
Episodes.Plot: A woman is forced to relive the same day over and over as she tries to prevent Mulder and Scully from being killed by her boyfriend during a bank robbery attempt. As the events restart again and again, Mulder's sense of Deja-vu grows stronger.
Episodes.GuestStars: Suanne Spoke, Monique Edwards, Wayne Alexander, David Michael Mullins, Mik Scriba, Carrie Hamilton, Darren E. Burrows

Episodes.Title: Arcadia
Episodes.Plot: On their first official case back on the X-Files, Mulder and Scully go undercover as a married couple at a prestigious planned community where several residents have recently disappeared after failing to comply with the rules and regulations.
Episodes.GuestStars: Peter White, Abraham Benrubi, Debra Christofferson, Tom Gallup, Marnie McPhail, Roger Morrissey, Tim Bagley, Tom Virtue, Juliana Donald, Mark Matthias

Episodes.Title: Alpha
Episodes.Plot: A mysterious dog thought to be the last of a rare Asian breed is responsible for several murders which Mulder and Scully are investigating. Now the agents have to find a way to stop the dog before it kills again.
Episodes.GuestStars: Melinda Culea, Thomas Duffy, Michael Mantell, David Starwalt, Andrew Robinson, James Michael Connor, Yau-Gene Chan, Tuan Tuan, Dana Lee, Lisa Picotte, Mady Levin, Treva Tegtmeier, Adrienne Wilde

Episodes.Title: Trevor
Episodes.Plot: After a tornado rips through a prison camp, one of the inmates disappears from solitary confinement and the prison warden is killed. As Mulder and Scully track him, he appears to have the power to pass through solid matter while changing its composition.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Diehl, Tuesday Knight, Frank Novak, David Bowe, Catherine Dent, Jeffrey Schoeny, Christopher Dahlberg, Robert Peters, Jerry Giles, Keith Brunsmann, Lamont Johnson, Cary Pfeffer, Terri Merryman, Lee Corbin

Episodes.Title: Milagro
Episodes.Plot: A writer living next to Mulder becomes obsessed with Scully and confesses to her that he is using her for a character in his novel. Scully finds herself strangely drawn to him even though he is now the prime suspect in the murder case that she and Mulder are investigating.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Hawkes, Nestor Serrano, Michael Bailey Smith, Angelo Vacco, Jillian Bach, Casey C. O'Neill, D. Bennett Nelson, Michelle Chaldau

Episodes.Title: The Unnatural
Episodes.Plot: Mulder meets with Agent Arthur Dales' brother (also named Arthur) and is told a tale of a talented negro baseball player from Roswell, New Mexico in the 1940's who may have been an alien that ran away from his colony because of his love for the game.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brian Thompson, Jesse L. Martin, Fredric Lehne, Lou Beatty Jr, Burnell Roques, Jesse James, M. Emmet Walsh, Lennie Lofton, Paul Willson, Walter T Phelan Jr., Gabriel Clifton, Al Kaplon, Robb Reesman, Daniel Duchov

Episodes.Title: Three of a Kind
Episodes.Plot: While on a stakeout of a Government Defense Convention in Las Vegas, The Lone Gunmen are reunited with Susanne Modeski, the mysterious woman who disappeared ten years earlier when they first met Agent Mulder.
Episodes.GuestStars: Signy Coleman, Charles Rocket, John Billingsley, Jim Fyfe, Michael McKean, George Sharperson, Brian Reddy, Phil Abrams, Richard Zobel, Jeff Bowser, Jason Felipe, Rick Garcia, Kalena Coleman

Episodes.Title: Field Trip
Episodes.Plot: When the bodies of a couple who have been missing for less than a week are discovered to have been reduced to bone, Mulder suggests that recent paranormal phenomena in the area may have caused the accelerated decomposition.
Episodes.GuestStars: Cody Weselis, Robyn Lively, David Denman, Jim Beaver

Episodes.Title: Biogenesis (1)
Episodes.Plot: Two scientists confer about each of their metal objects that were found in Africa and they theorize that the objects are pieces of a puzzle which could be undeniable proof that human, plant, and animal life did not originate on this planet. When one of the scientists is killed and the objects are stolen, the agents investigate and Mulder begins to experience severe neurological pain caused by the objects.
Episodes.GuestStars: Sheila Tousey, Warren Sweeney, Chet Grissom, Marty Zagon, Samuel Kwaku Minta, Ayo Adeyemi, Benjamin Ochieng, Murray Rubinstein, Michael Chinyamurindi, Michael Ensign
